===========
ansible-dir
===========

NAME
	ansible-dir - create, populate, and manage an ansible directory

SYNOPSIS
	ansible-dir [-h] [-d basedir] [--version] command

DESCRIPTION
	Create, populate, and manage an ansible directory in accordance with the
	AnsibleWorks Best Practices.

	See: http://www.ansibleworks.com/docs/bestpractices.html

OPTIONS
	-h or --help
		Display a help message and exit.

	-d basedir 
		Specify the base directory on which to operate (default: ansible).

	--version
		Display the version and ext.

COMMANDS
  	init	initialize an ansible directory

